{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"662d75ae-8a45-49d8-a3a5-bf7921687dce","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9dd82408-bb3c-43c9-baa8-cdd78b67cbe6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"0C0B:3B272C:3B2B5B:44CF3E:69F00C6D"},"id":"057f0ed1-038a-4279-92fc-b84845e273ae","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:25:06.471Z","parentId":"8addd89e-4148-4da8-bd65-3f92e9c91185"}
